---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service — Fimil" description="Terms of service for the Fimil platform.">
  <article class="py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <a href="/legal" class="text-sm text-fimil-600 hover:text-fimil-700">&larr; Legal</a>
      <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">Effective Date: March 1, 2026</p>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-600">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            By accessing or using the Fimil platform ("Service"), you agree to be bound by these
            Terms of Service. If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">2. Description of Service</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Fimil provides a unified application security platform that orchestrates open-source
            security scanners and provides a consolidated dashboard for managing security findings.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">3. User Accounts</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and
            for all activities under your account.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">4. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            You agree to use the Service only for lawful purposes and in compliance with our <a
              href="/legal/acceptable-use-policy"
              class="text-fimil-600">Acceptable Use Policy</a
            >.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">5. Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            The Service and its original content, features, and functionality are owned by Fimil
            Inc. and are protected by applicable intellectual property laws.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, Fimil Inc. shall not be liable for any indirect,
            incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">7. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Material changes will be
            communicated via the Service or email.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900">8. Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-2">
            Questions about these terms? Contact us at <a
              href="mailto:legal@fimil.dev"
              class="text-fimil-600">legal@fimil.dev</a
            >.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
